/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_harborseal_ver04/data/2017218598/00279525784/1914022101/0378.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/2017218598/1914-02-21/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_harborseal_ver04/data/2017218598/00279525784/1914022101/0378.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/2017218598/1914-02-21/ed-1/?sp=4"], "batch": ["ak_harborseal_ver04"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/alaska/", "3/united states/alaska/seward/"], "contributor": ["alaska state library historical collections"], "date": "1914-02-21", "dates": ["1914-02-21"], "description": ["The work of decorating Brown Hawkins hall for the big party tonight has been completed and the big bail room is a bower of beauty The dance bids fair to surpass anything of its kind that has ever been held in Seward and promises to usher in the dawn of the long waited for prosperity in a manner fitting to the occasion and worthy of the two business houses wiio are combining tonight to entertain the residents of the Kenai peninsula Arrangements have been made to dntertain the largest crowd in the history of Seward and not one thing has been left undone that could possibly add to the pleasure or enjoyment of the guests even to providing dainty and appropriate souvenirs of the oc casion that will be presented to all who attend Dancing will begin at 9 p m Frank J Cotter and Sidney Ander son both drawn for jury duty at Cor dova for the March term of court have been excused from attendance by Judge Brown I Mrs Charles Krefting and daughter Elinore Marion are doing nicely ac cording to Dr Baughman and will soon be out to take advantage of the early spring weather that"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-05-22T12:59:50.539Z", "group": ["ndnp/ak", "alaska-state-library-historical-collections-awardee"], "h